# data/egx30.csv is INTENTIONALLY tracked, not ignored. It is a seed/
# fallback cache for egx30_benchmark.py, not user data: on a cold start
# (e.g. Render's ephemeral filesystem) with no cache present, a blocked
# or failed download raises RuntimeError with nothing to fall back to.
# The committed file is a floor, not a source of truth — it gets
# overwritten on the first successful refresh.
